snippet.title: Indians In Summer Vacation | Ft. Tena Jaiin | The Paayal Jain
snippet.description:
Hey Guys ,
This Video all the things that happen in summer vacations . Every Indian in summer vacations going on vacation with family to hill stations like shimla , manali , mussoorie , darjeeling , haridwar , rishikesh . Indian moms dealing with holiday homework given by school teachers during summer break , Family trips , horse ridding , trekking , hiking . watching sunsets , sunrise at famous hill tops , creating memories clicking pictures , tourist locations and rush of people and traffic jams , mother excited to go vacation getting her beauty regime by parlour didi , waxing , facial , threading , bleach , dtan , shopping from sarojini nagar to travel , buying gifts for relatives on vacay , travelling by train enjoying , singing eating train food , road trip with family , stopping at dhaba , mom feeding her home cooked food puri aloo jeera sabzi , middle class dad driving on highway , kids singing fighting taking pictures on the way to himachal and so much more ..
This video is filled with such memories and situations we all have been in. 
Relish and Relive your Childhood Memories.. You will have major nostalgia

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. snippet.title: bye, from Dream.
snippet.description:
bye, from Dream. I deleted my face reveal, and this is why.

After face revealing and removing my mask, I regretted the attention and hate, and am walking it back.


Pre-save Until I End Up Dead: https://presave.umusic.com/dream

Follow my socials:
â½ Twitter - @dream
â½ Instagram - @dreamwastaken
â½ Snapchat - @dreampublic

I will slowly be deleting all pictures of me online, and going back to just being a gamer in a mask. Starting with my Mr Beast Video, and my Face Reveal video, "hi, I'm Dream". I will be walking it back. I will be getting rid of everything other than my new mask.

The same company that made the spider man mask, batman mask, and many other superheroes, made me a mask so that I can be Dream all of the time. Hide my identity, even if public, at McDonalds, or any place I need to go.

thank you all from the bottom of my heart to those that supported me, even though I am ugly. I appreciate you all more than you could ever know, and I will be working on my face while I'm masked again.

snippet.description:
Shekhar Jaiswal Presents New Bholenath Song "Japle Om Namaha Shivay"

Shekhar Jaiswal Instagram - https://www.instagram.com/theshekharjaiswal

Singer, Composer, Lyrics - Shekhar Jaiswal
Music - GW Music Studio Rudrapur (Saif)
Cast - Shekhar Jaiswal, Sameer, Muneer, Aman
Direction & Dop - Soumya Jaiswal
Location - Sattal, Jageshwar, Haldwani
Edited By - Shekhar Jaiswal

Another Channel - https://youtube.com/c/ShekharJaiswalComedy

Booking - 9719998366, 7451940400
Shekharredifmail@gmail.com


Lyrics -
-----------------------------------------
Purab se suraj nikle
Tere darsh ki pyas jagaye
mandir ki ghanti baje
Teri or khicha chala aaye
Tere darshan se bhole baba 
Mera din ban jaye re

Tera pal pal bita jaye re
Japle tu namah shivay
Om namah shivay om namah shivay..

Tan ko to dhoya magar man na dhoya
Kahe jape tu ye maala..x2
Jhute dikhawe ka sone sa chamke
Andar se man tera kala
Thoda to ruk mere bande, shiv prem ko man me jgale
Shrdha se jal ko chada ke, bhole ke darshan pale
Jitna bhi karle, Jeb tu bharle, daulat sath na jaye re..

Tera pal pal bita jaye re
Japle tu namah shivay
Om namah shivay om namah shivay..

Na jane kis bhesh me aakr mera sb kar jata hai
Jo bhi mangu bhole se wo chupke se de jata hai
Teri maya tu jane hum to tere diwane
Tera naam hi meri dawa hai, is baat ko koi na jane
Shekhar ke shankar, kankar kankar
Tujhko rah dikhaye re

Tera pal pal bita jaye re
Japle tu namah shivay
Om namah shivay om namah shivay..

Episode 1666: Guest For Khushi
--------------------
Jethalal is off to attend a seminar and Daya gets good news. A very important guest is about to arrive in Gokuldham society to meet Khushi.

Show Name- Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
Star Cast -  Dilip Joshi, Disha Vakani, Amit Bhatt, Shailesh Lodha
Full Episode - 63
Produced By - Asit Modi

#TaarakMehtaKaOoltahChashmah #à¤¤à¤¾à¤°à¤•à¤®à¥‡à¤¹à¤¤à¤¾à¤•à¤¾à¤‰à¤²à¥à¤Ÿà¤¾à¤šà¤¶à¥à¤®à¤¾ #SAB

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - Promoolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalaal.

Click to watch all the episodes of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL6Rtnh6YJK7a6aWvIzLwbDe6FzzowRhMq

snippet.title: Everything Is F*cKED | PAIN à¤•à¥€ à¤¤à¤¾à¤•à¤¤ à¤œà¤¾à¤¨ à¤²à¥‹ | SeeKen Book Summary
snippet.description:
EVERYTHING IS F*@KED! BOOK SUMMARY IN HINDI BY SEEKEN

ART OF NOT GIVING A F BOOK: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GOOAyX2f1TQ&t=325s

Time Stamp

00:00 - Researchers' Story
01:14 - The Blue Dot Effect
05:08 - Witold Pilecki story 
08:58 - Everything is F&@$ 
09:44 - The uncomfortable truth
12:09 - Sense of Control 
12:29 - A Believe in the value of something 
12:42 - A community of people who share your values 
12:59 - Elon Musk Example

What if there doesn't exist anything called pain? Would you take it if you are given only happiness and not any of the sadness?
Agar summer season mein garmi nahi hoti toh ice- cream ka maja kaise lete?
Similarly, if your life is not fucked up, if something doesn't bother you, you cannot change your life.
In my latest video, I have discussed this topic. I have explained how pain can be utilized as a tool for progress, without any contribution from happiness.
I have incorporated examples and strategies from the book "Everything is Fucked" by Mark manson.
I delved into various methods and experiments aimed at how hope develops a sense of purpose in life.

snippet.title: How to Stop wasting your life |Dopamine Detox using brain waves| 21 days Challenge to Dopamine Detox
snippet.description:
Aapko pata hi hai ki aap kya karte ho.

Insta ya Youtube ke shorts me ek baar enter kar gaye to bas scroll karte rehte ho.

Chahe hamne ye socha ho ki ham thak chuke hai aur hame 5 minute ka break chahiye ya phir ye socha ho ki bas ek do instagram reels ya youtube shorts dekh ke vaapis kaam karne lag jaayenge. 

Phir bas ham scroll kar rahe hai ek aur ek aur karte karte 2-3 hours ho gaye hai aur hame pata hi nhi chala. Aaj ka din dobara khatam ho gaya , life me kuch karna tha, kuch bade sapne the, lekin aaj ham kuch nhi kar paaye, ek guilt ke saath ham so jaate hai. Aur ek ke baad ek din ham aise hi waste kari jaa rahe hai saal me 365 din hai * 2-2.5 hours per day = almost 1000 hours ham ek saal ham isi me waste kar rahe hai. Jisme ham apne maa baap, apne teachers aur sabse important khud ke sapne pure kar sakte the lekin aaj hamne phir inhe miss kar diya.
.... I hope you will love this video.

Jai Hind

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Raj Anankat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or be prepared to leave the premises.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Raj Anankat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or be prepared to leave the premises.

               Yeh kahani hai ek sanyukt parivaar mai rehnewale Modi khaandaan ki. Izzatdaar, ameer aur naamcheen hone ke bawajud, ghar ke sanskaar aur sanskriti hain inka saccha dhan. Iss ghar ko chalati hai choti bahu, Kokilaben jissey darte hain saare sadasya. Kokilaben ke bade bete, Ahem ki shaadi hojati hai Gopi se joh hai ek saaf dil ki siddhi saadhi, anpapdh ladki. Unke jethani ke bete, Jigar ki shaadi hojati hai Gopi ki behen, Raashi se joh hai bohot hi chaalaak aur nakhrel. 
              Raashi hamesha dikhati hai neecha Gopi ko aur karti hai uske liye mushkilen taiyaar. Par Gopi ka haath thama Kokilaben ne aur banaya ussey hoshiyaar. Iss saas-bahu ki jodi ne apne pyaar, dulaar aur balidaan se bandhe rakha hai Modi parivaar ko.
